Package wah.giovann.csvhandler

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CSVArray
    The CSVArray class is a collection CSVRecord objects that represents the contents of at .csv file.
    CSVFileFormat
    CSVFileFormat allows for the specification of input and/or output .csv file formats.
    CSVFileFormat.Builder
    A builder class used to construct a CSVFileFormat object.

    For example, to build an input CSVFileFormat instance that reads from a file with UTF-16 encoding, semicolon delimiters, and no header, the following code would work:

      CSVFileFormat format = new CSVFileFormat.Builder()
       .characterSetName(CSVFileFormat.UTF_16_CHARSET)
       .delimiter(CSVFileFormat.SEMICOLON_DELIMITER)
       .hasHeader(false)
       .build();

    Note that if the character set name for an input file is not specified, the CSVReader will attempt to determine it automatically.
    CSVReader
    The CSVReader class is responsible for reading of information from .csv files.
    CSVRecord
    The CSVRecord class represents a row of data in a .csv file.
    CSVWriter
    CSVWriter is a very simple class used to quickly write a CSVArray instance to file.
